ndic Women includes many works translated for the first time from their original Icelandic, and rescues from obscurity the voices and experiences of women as they struggled in a new country. It offers insight into the many obstacles, both personal and professional, that faced these pioneering writers. An introduction by Kirsten Wolf provides a literary and historical context, and is complemented by photographs and brief author biographies.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 7aLITERARY COLLECTIONS / Canadian.2bisacsh1 aWolf, Kirsten, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010z978311127416408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010z978311127724040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978088755398140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780887553981423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780887553981/original  a978-3-11-127416-4  ACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010b2010  a978-3-11-127724-0  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010b2010  aGBV-deGruyter-alles